    "long_instructions": "## AI as a Hospital Triage Nurse\r\n\r\nUse AI Chat to choose which two patients to assist first. \r\n\r\n### Do This:\r\n\r\n1. **Copy and paste** the prompt below into AI Chat. Press **Send** and read AI Chat's response. \r\n\r\n::: details [**Click to expand the AI Chat prompt**]\r\n>You are a hospital triage nurse. Read these six patient profiles and choose which two I should help first. Explain why you selected these two patients.\r\n>\r\nName: Maria \r\nAge: 5\r\nType of Injury: Deep forehead cut from a fall at the playground\r\nPain Level (out of 10): 6\r\nTreatment Needed: Stitches, cleaning and dressing the wound, tetanus shot\r\n>\r\nName: James \r\nAge: 23\r\nType of Injury: Concussion from a car accident\r\nPain Level (out of 10): 5\r\nTreatment Needed: Neurological exam, CT scan, pain management, observation for 24 hours\r\n>\r\nName: Evelyn \r\nAge: 42\r\nType of Injury: Severe allergic reaction (anaphylaxis) from shellfish\r\nPain Level (out of 10): 8\r\nTreatment Needed: Epinephrine injection, IV fluids, oxygen support, observation for several hours\r\n>\r\nName: Hassan \r\nAge: 67\r\nType of Injury: Chest pain, possible heart attack\r\nPain Level (out of 10): 9\r\nTreatment Needed: ECG, blood tests, oxygen, nitroglycerin, immediate cardiology consultation\r\n>\r\nName: Olivia \r\nAge: 30\r\nType of Injury: Third-degree burn on hand from kitchen accident\r\nPain Level (out of 10): 7\r\nTreatment Needed: IV pain relief, burn dressing, possible skin graft consultation\r\n>\r\nName: Dante \r\nAge: 15\r\nType of Injury: Sprained ankle from basketball game\r\nPain Level (out of 10): 5\r\nTreatment Needed: X-ray, compression wrap, ice, crutches\r\n>\r\n:::\r\n\r\n2. Find the section in your Activity Guide called \"AI’s Selections\" and answer the questions.\r\n3. Revise your prompt to AI Chat and have it prioritize the same things you did. For example, try:\r\n\r\n::: details [**Click to expand the AI Chat prompt**]\r\n>Now make your selection by prioritizing younger patients and patients with high pain levels.\r\n:::\r\n**Try it out!**\r\n",
